description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exciting opportunity to join The College Practice, a forward thinking GP surgery located in Maidstone.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, positive, dedicated GP (with partnership opportunities) to join our large, friendly, knowledgeable multidisciplinary team, supported by a compliment of dedicated administrative staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a high performing forward thinking GP training practice with a strong ethos of continuity of patient care, team work and peer support. We have a list size of circa 20,000 patients, use Vision and our most recent CQC rating was GOOD. We operate on a mixture of clinical triage, multidisciplinary working and customised session lengths to suit individual clinician’s means that both patients and clinicians are happy. We understand that multimodal consultations can be daunting at first – full induction and training is offered and applicants are welcome to speak to current clinicians who all enjoy this way of working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;What we offer Salaried GP’s;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any combination of sessions from 1 per week to full-time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full indemnity paid and up to £10k per session&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible start and finish times and flexible session length too&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No duty sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A contract based on the BMA model contract with ample time for admin&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous salary, 6 weeks annual leave, one week study leave. 182 hours of CPD per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to develop teaching or minor surgery interest if desired&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A resilient approach to workload and reduction of inappropriate demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would be interested in joining as a Partner and contribute to the future and strategic direction of the Practice, then please contact Angela Warren via email at a.warren3@nhs.net or call 01622 776912&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Other benefits include;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Occupational sick pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle To Work scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Special Leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Safeguarding Statement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The College Practice is committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of vulnerable adults, children and young people, and expects all staff to share this commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have robust safeguarding policies and procedures, including a Freedom to Speak Up policy which enables staff to raise any concerns confidentially&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Disclosure and Barring Service Check&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to the Rehabilitation of Offenders Act (Exceptions Order) 1975 and as such it will be necessary for a submission for Disclosure to be made to the Disclosure and Barring Service (formerly known as CRB) to check for any previous criminal convictions&lt;/p&gt;
